body:
The error says that ``` the trait bound `MyTrait + 'static: std::clone::Clone` is not satisfied ``` but that an implementation of `MyTrait + 'static as std::clone::Clone` *was* found.

```rust
trait MyTrait {}

impl Clone for MyTrait {
    fn clone(&self) -> Self {
        unimplemented!()
    }
}

fn main() {}
```

```
error[E0277]: the trait bound `MyTrait + 'static: std::clone::Clone` is not satisfied
 --> src/main.rs:3:6
  |
3 | impl Clone for MyTrait {
  |      ^^^^^ the trait `std::clone::Clone` is not implemented for `MyTrait + 'static`
  |
  = help: the following implementations were found:
            <MyTrait + 'static as std::clone::Clone>
```

It may have to do with Clone being a lang item because the message is better if I do the same with my own Clone trait. At least the error include ``` `MyTrait + 'static` does not have a constant size known at compile-time ```.

```rust
trait MyTrait {}

trait MyClone: Sized {
    fn clone(&self) -> Self;
}

impl MyClone for MyTrait {
    fn clone(&self) -> Self {
        unimplemented!()
    }
}

fn main() {}
```

```
error[E0277]: the trait bound `MyTrait + 'static: std::marker::Sized` is not satisfied
 --> src/main.rs:7:6
  |
7 | impl MyClone for MyTrait {
  |      ^^^^^^^ `MyTrait + 'static` does not have a constant size known at compile-time
  |
  = help: the trait `std::marker::Sized` is not implemented for `MyTrait + 'static`
```

- rustc 1.25.0-nightly (51b0b3734 2018-01-12)
